Revision history for Date-Parse-Modern

1.0    2026-01-20

	- Properly handle datetimes on the EXACT epoch (1970-01-01 00:00:00)

	- Allow external changes to the separator variable

	- Add a script to generate the TZ code to offset hash

	- Support AM/PM and a timezone

	- Make sure we only capture valid years (not +1000/-1000)

0.8    2025-11-07

	- Add support for days with st, nd, rd, th suffixes

	- Add support for the uncommon format YYYY-M-D and D-M-YYYY (single digit month/day)

0.6    2024-01-15

	- Minor bugfix for detecting years in non-standard formats
		- Fixes: 25/Jan/2023:11:15:40 -0800
		- Fixes: dec 21 94 17:05 -1700

0.5    2023-10-13

	- Code cleanup and a couple of minor format additions.

0.4    2023-02-01

	- Support for two new string forms

	- Require Time::Local 1.26 because that's where timegm_local() was introduced

	- Handle error messages a little better

	- Better handle milliseconds, because they were breaking on Windows

	- Lots of work done on unit tests to make them work on older Perl's and Windows

0.3    2023-01-26

	- 99% format parity with Date::Parse

	- Better debugging

	- Better memory usage for caching

	- Tons of code cleanup and comments

0.2    2023-01-14

	- Documentation updates

	- Debug cleanup and normalizing

	- Support more string formats

	- Make the unit tests more verbose for failures

	- Add an option to benchmark individual strings against Date::Parse

	- Add GitHub CI testing

	- Cache local TZ offset lookups for a major speed increase

0.1    2023-01-13

	- First version, released on an unsuspecting world.
